{"name":"callbacks.add","type":"method","title":"callbacks.add()","desc":"Add a callback or a collection of callbacks to a callback list.","categories":["callbacks-object","version/1.7"],"entries":[{"return":"Callbacks","signatures":{"added":"1.7","argument":{"desc":"A function, or array of functions, that are to be added to the callback list.","name":"callbacks","type":"Function, Array"}},"examples":null,"longdesc":"\n    <p>This method returns the Callbacks object onto which it is attached (<code>this</code>). </p>\n    <h2 id=\"example-1\">Example</h2>\n    <p>Use <code>callbacks.add()</code> to add new callbacks to a callback list:</p>\n    <pre><code><![CDATA[// a sample logging function to be added to a callbacks list\nvar foo = function( value ) {\n  console.log( \"foo: \" + value );\n};\n\n// another function to also be added to the list\nvar bar = function( value ){\n  console.log( \"bar: \" + value );\n};\n\nvar callbacks = $.Callbacks();\n\n// add the function \"foo\" to the list\ncallbacks.add( foo );\n\n// fire the items on the list\ncallbacks.fire( \"hello\" );\n// outputs: \"foo: hello\"\n\n// add the function \"bar\" to the list\ncallbacks.add( bar );\n\n// fire the items on the list again\ncallbacks.fire( \"world\" );\n\n// outputs:\n// \"foo: world\"\n// \"bar: world\"\n]]></code>\n</pre>\n  "}]}